This is a missed-optimization in BDCE.

The following program reveals the missed optimization.
The source program is
```llvm
define void @and(i64 %a) {
entry:
  %and = and i64 %a, 24
  %ret1 = and i64 %and, 8
  %ret2 = and i64 %and, 16
  call void @use(i64 %ret1)
  call void @use(i64 %ret2)
  ret void
}

declare void @use(i64)

```

However, current LLVM cannot optimize the source program. The expected optimized program is
```llvm
define void @and(i64 %a) {
entry:
  %ret1 = and i64 %a, 8
  %ret2 = and i64 %a, 16
  call void @use(i64 %ret1)
  call void @use(i64 %ret2)
  ret void
}

declare void @use(i64)

